[3] 1st case in Hunan
Date: Sat 27 Apr 2013
Source: English News, Xinhua report [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/health/2013-04/27/c_132345696.htm


First H7N9 human infection reported in Hunan Province
-----------------------------------------------------
Health authorities in central China's Hunan Province on Saturday confirmed its first human infection case of H7N9 bird flu. A 64-year-old woman, a resident in Shaoyang City, started suffering from a fever on 14 April 2013, and laboratory tests confirmed her H7N9 infection on Saturday [27 Apr 2013], Hunan Provincial Health Department said in a statement. The statement said the woman had been exposed to poultry 4 days before she developed the fever. No abnormal symptoms had been found among the 41 people who were in close contact with her, it added.

An official with the department said the woman had been critically ill but that her condition was improving.

